# JavaScript Architecture Rules

Keep modules focused and predictable.

## `calculator.js`

- Only math calculations.
- No DOM access.
- No localStorage access.

## `datetime.js`

- Handle time rules:
  - lunch break skip
  - working hours boundaries
  - skip Sunday
  - **deadline algorithm**

## `storage.js`

- Handle save/load to localStorage.
- Provide small API (get/set/loadTasks/saveTasks, etc.).
- Never manipulate DOM here.

## `ui.js`

- DOM queries and rendering only:
  - dashboard cards
  - progress bar
  - task cards
- Should call calculator/datetime/storage APIs.

## `app.js`

- Wire everything together.
- Initialize state, load tasks, start realtime loop.

